				\begin{document}$${\text{Cells}}\,{\text{viablity}} = \frac{{({\text{O}}.{\text{D}}({\text{C}} + {\text{B}}) - {\text{O}}.{\text{B}}({\text{B}}))}}{{({\text{O}}.{\text{D}}({\text{C}}) - {\text{O}}.{\text{D}}({\text{empty}}))}} \times 100$$\end{document}Cellsviablity=(O.D(C+B)-O.B(B))(O.D(C)-O.D(empty))×100where O.D(C + B) is the absorbance measured with a given concentration of Lactobacillus strains adhered on Vero cells, O.D(B) is the absorbance measured for the control well containing bacteria without Vero cells, and O.D(C) is the absorbance measured for control untreated mock-infected cells.
